<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,1479,2009]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1732,1756]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Alcock, 1900)" baseAuthorityName="Alcock" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[330,691,1732,1756]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Opusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis box="[330,497,1732,1756]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Opusia indica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Alcock, A." box="[521,683,1732,1756]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="279 - 456" refId="ref44374" refString="Alcock, A. (1900) Material for a carcinological Fauna of India. No. 6: The Brachyura Catometopa, or Grapsoidea. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 69 (2), 279 - 456." type="journal article" year="1900">Alcock, 1900</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Alcock, A." box="[933,1104,1732,1756]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="279 - 456" refId="ref44374" refString="Alcock, A. (1900) Material for a carcinological Fauna of India. No. 6: The Brachyura Catometopa, or Grapsoidea. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 69 (2), 279 - 456." type="journal article" year="1900">Alcock (1900)</bibRefCitation>
from Karachi, 
<collectingCountry box="[1302,1397,1732,1756]" name="Pakistan" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1900" box="[151,346,1768,1792]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Tylodiplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis box="[151,346,1768,1792]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Tylodiplax indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Rahayu, D. L. &amp; Naser, M. D." box="[362,544,1767,1792]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref51169" refString="Ng, P. K. L., Rahayu, D. L. &amp; Naser, M. D. (2009) The Campatndriidae of Iraq, with description of a new genus and notes on Leptochryseus Al-khayat &amp; Jones, 1996 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura). Zootaxa, 2312, 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="2009">
Ng 
<emphasis box="[404,454,1768,1792]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. (2009)
</bibRefCitation>
recently have described the monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. K. L. Ng, Rahayu &amp; Naser" authorityYear="2009" box="[1069,1150,1768,1792]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Opusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1069,1150,1768,1792]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Opusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and recorded the species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1900" box="[151,257,1804,1828]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Tylodiplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis box="[151,171,1804,1828]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[187,257,1804,1828]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[330,379,1804,1827]" name="Iraq" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Iraq</collectingCountry>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Rahayu, D. L. &amp; Naser, M. D." box="[550,737,1804,1828]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref51169" refString="Ng, P. K. L., Rahayu, D. L. &amp; Naser, M. D. (2009) The Campatndriidae of Iraq, with description of a new genus and notes on Leptochryseus Al-khayat &amp; Jones, 1996 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura). Zootaxa, 2312, 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="2009">
Ng 
<emphasis box="[593,644,1804,1828]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. (2009)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. K. L. Ng, Rahayu &amp; Naser" authorityYear="2009" box="[751,832,1804,1828]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Opusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[751,832,1804,1828]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Opusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mainly characterized by a broadly ovate carapace without distinct ridges on dorsal surface (such ridges are seen in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Man, 1895 [in de Man, 1895-" authorityYear="1898" box="[876,994,1840,1864]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Tylodiplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[876,994,1840,1864]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Tylodiplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), anterolateral margin making no angle with posterolateral margin, the anterior part of the first two thoracic sternites of males are rounded (v.s. triangular in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Man, 1895 [in de Man, 1895-" authorityYear="1898" box="[183,301,1912,1936]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Tylodiplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[183,301,1912,1936]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Tylodiplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), a distinct complete suture between male abdominal segments, segments 3-5 functionally fused, abdominal segment 5 basically constricted, male G1 ending in a conical apex. Detailed morphological and taxonomic remarks for this genus and allied genera are given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Rahayu, D. L. &amp; Naser, M. D." box="[876,1058,1984,2009]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref51169" refString="Ng, P. K. L., Rahayu, D. L. &amp; Naser, M. D. (2009) The Campatndriidae of Iraq, with description of a new genus and notes on Leptochryseus Al-khayat &amp; Jones, 1996 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura). Zootaxa, 2312, 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="2009">
Ng 
<emphasis box="[917,967,1984,2008]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. (2009)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
